BT 1 0 0 1 0 110 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL (Further, GEO introduces a flexible framework for defining visibility metrics tailor-made for) Tj T* (generative engines as the notion of visibility in generative engines is more nuanced and) Tj T* (multi-faceted than traditional search engines \(Figure 3\). While average ranking on the response) Tj T* (page is a good measure of visibility in traditional search engines, which present a linear list of) Tj T* (websites, this does not apply to generative engines. Generative Engines provide rich, structured) Tj T* (responses and embed websites as inline citations in the response, often embedding them with) Tj T* (different lengths, at varying positions, and with diverse styles. This necessitates the need for) Tj T* (visibility metrics tailor-made for generative engines, which measure the visibility of attributed) Tj T* (sources over multiple dimensions, such as relevance and influence of citation to query, measured) Tj T* (through both an objective and a subjective lens.) Tj T* ET
